<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.bolivialine.com/bolivia/newsletter/Newsletter200511.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.bolivialine.com/bolivia/newsletter/Newsletter200511.htm" rel="nofollow">"All Saints day in Bolivia - "The skull festival""</a>. Bolivia Line (November 2005)<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.bolivialine.com/bolivia/newsletter/Newsletter200511.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.bolivialine.com/bolivia/newsletter/Newsletter200511.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.bolivialine.com/bolivia/newsletter/Newsletter200511.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-20</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=All+Saints+day+in+Bolivia+-+%22The+skull+festival%22&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=Bolivia+Line+%28November+2005%29&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bolivialine.com%2Fbolivia%2Fnewsletter%2FNewsletter200511.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Day_of_the_Dead"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
