<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.italymag.co.uk/2005/news-from-italy/lifestyle/halloween-and-the-day-of-the-dead-in-italy/" class="external text" title="http://www.italymag.co.uk/2005/news-from-italy/lifestyle/halloween-and-the-day-of-the-dead-in-italy/" rel="nofollow">All Saints Day celebrations in Italy</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.warsawvoice.pl/view/3970/" class="external text" title="http://www.warsawvoice.pl/view/3970/" rel="nofollow">Polish observance</a> Accessed June 11, 2007.</li>
<li id="cite_note-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.virtualtourist.com/travel/Europe/Hungary/Budapest_Fovaros/Budapest-436839/Local_Customs-Budapest-BR-8.html" class="external text" title="http://www.virtualtourist.com/travel/Europe/Hungary/Budapest_Fovaros/Budapest-436839/Local_Customs-Budapest-BR-8.html" rel="nofollow">Slovakia observance</a>. Accessed June 11, 2007.</li>
<li id="cite_note-19"><b><a href="#cite_ref-19" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.virtualtourist.com/travel/Europe/Hungary/Budapest_Fovaros/Budapest-436839/Local_Customs-Budapest-BR-8.html" class="external text" title="http://www.virtualtourist.com/travel/Europe/Hungary/Budapest_Fovaros/Budapest-436839/Local_Customs-Budapest-BR-8.html" rel="nofollow">Hungary observance</a>. Accessed June 11, 2007.</li>
<li id="cite_note-20"><b><a href="#cite_ref-20" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://ausis.gf.vu.lt/eka/customs/velines.html" class="external text" title="http://ausis.gf.vu.lt/eka/customs/velines.html" rel="nofollow">Lithuanian observance</a>. Accessed June 11, 2007</li>
<li id="cite_note-21"><b><a href="#cite_ref-21" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.everyculture.com/Cr-Ga/Croatia.html" class="external text" title="http://www.everyculture.com/Cr-Ga/Croatia.html" rel="nofollow">Croatian observance</a>. Accessed June 11, 2007</li>
<li id="cite_note-22"><b><a href="#cite_ref-22" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.kapitelj.com/vsi_sveti_1.november_dan_mrtvih.html" class="external text" title="http://www.kapitelj.com/vsi_sveti_1.november_dan_mrtvih.html" rel="nofollow">Slovenian observance</a>. Accessed November 5, 2007.</li>
<li id="cite_note-23"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/travel/2004/oct/26/romania" class="external text" title="http://www.guardian.co.uk/travel/2004/oct/26/romania" rel="nofollow">Romanian observance</a>. Accessed June 11, 2007.</li>
<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> See <a href="/wiki/All_Saints_Day" title="All Saints Day" class="mw-redirect">All Saints Day</a>, <a href="/wiki/All_Souls_Day" title="All Souls Day" class="mw-redirect">All Souls Day</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://english.ohmynews.com/articleview/article_view.asp?article_class=5&amp;no=314183&amp;rel_no=1" class="external text" title="http://english.ohmynews.com/articleview/article_view.asp?article_class=5&amp;no=314183&amp;rel_no=1" rel="nofollow">Nepali holiday honoring the dead</a>. Accessed June 11, 2007</li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://lucy.ukc.ac.uk/Fdtl/Ancestors/kopytoff.html" class="external text" title="http://lucy.ukc.ac.uk/Fdtl/Ancestors/kopytoff.html" rel="nofollow">African ancestor ritual</a>; <a href="http://iunona.pmf.ukim.edu.mk/etnoantropozum/Kovach%20Senka-angl.htm" class="external text" title="http://iunona.pmf.ukim.edu.mk/etnoantropozum/Kovach%20Senka-angl.htm" rel="nofollow">Importance in many traditional religions throughout all of Africa serve as communications with ancestors</a></li>
</ol>
</div>
<p><a name="Further_reading" id="Further_reading"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Day_of_the_Dead&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFBrandes2006">Brandes, Stanley (2006-12-15). <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=rlyTyVbhBYUC&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;hl=fr" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=rlyTyVbhBYUC&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;hl=fr" rel="nofollow">Skulls to the Living, Bread to the Dead</a></i>. Blackwell Publishing. pp.&#160;232. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1405152478" class="internal">ISBN 1405152478</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=rlyTyVbhBYUC&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;hl=fr" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=rlyTyVbhBYUC&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;hl=fr" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=rlyTyVbhBYUC&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;hl=fr</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-05-14</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Skulls+to+the+Living%2C+Bread+to+the+Dead&amp;rft.aulast=Brandes&amp;rft.aufirst=Stanley&amp;rft.au=Brandes%2C+Stanley&amp;rft.date=2006-12-15&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B232&amp;rft.pub=Blackwell+Publishing&amp;rft.isbn=1405152478&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DrlyTyVbhBYUC%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%26hl%3Dfr&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Day_of_the_Dead"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li>_____. "The Day of the Dead, Halloween, and the Quest for Mexican National Identity." <i>Journal of American Folklore</i> 442 (1998)&#160;: 359-80.</li>
<li>_____. "Sugar, Colonialism, and Death: On the Origins of Mexico's Day of the Dead" <i>Comparative Studies in Sociology and History</i> 39.2 (1997): 270-299</li>
<li>_____. "Iconogaphy in Mexico's Day of the Dead." <i>Ethnohistory</i> 45.2(1998):181-218</li>
<li>Carmichael, Elizabeth. Sayer, Chloe. <i>The Skeleton at the Feast: The Day of the Dead in Mexico</i>. Great Britain: The Bath Press, 1991.</li>
<li>Conklin, Paul. "Death Takes A Holiday." <i>U.S. Catholic</i> 66 (2001)&#160;: 38-41.</li>
<li>Garcia-Rivera, Alex. "Death Takes a Holiday." <i>U.S. Catholic</i> 62 (1997)&#160;: 50.</li>
<li>Roy, Ann. "A Crack Between the Worlds." <i>Commonwealth</i> 122 (1995)&#160;: 13-16</li>
<li>Shawn D. Haley and Curt Fukuda <i>Day of the Dead: When Two Worlds Meet in Oaxaca</i>, Berhahn Books, 2004.</li>
</ul>
